Content:: This is a list of timelines currently on Wikipedia. There are several types of timeline articles. Timespans next to the timeline articles listed here include the date of the earliest item included in the linked timeline article. The following is a list of fictional timelines. The Cosmic Calendar is a method to visualize the chronology of the universe, scaling its current age of 13.8 billion years to a single year in order to help intuit it for pedagogical purposes in science education or popular science.
